# Pit local state + runtime caches (hindsight, repo-map, frequent-files, interrupted-subagent
# resume snapshots) — per-cwd, never versioned. Exception: .pit/agents/ holds curated, reusable
# subagent type definitions (like .claude/agents/), which ARE meant to be versioned.
.pit/*
!.pit/agents/
# Same caches under any package (e.g. packages/coding-agent/.pit/repo-map.jsonl).
# Use a contents glob (not a dir glob) so the agents/ whitelist still applies.
**/.pit/*
!**/.pit/agents/

# Scratch analysis artifacts (local-only, not part of the project)
RELATORIO-*.md
pkglist.txt
*.pre-cleanup.bak

# Generated thumbnail cache (hyperframes presentation)
hyperframes-pit-presentation/.thumbnails/

# Nested reference clone (its own git repo — not part of this monorepo)
everything-claude-code/
